extremely common in homer:
κόρη
γυνή γυναικός, ἡ
πατήρ πατρός, ὁ
μήτηρ μητρός, ἡ
τέκνον τέκνου, τό - child
  https://archive.org/details/childrenshomerad00colu/page/102/mode/2up
  Hector and Andromache are parents, baby is Astyanax
παῖς παιδός, ὁ/ἡ -- lemmatizer works on παιδός, but not on παῖς
υἱός υἱοῦ, ὁ - son
θυγάτηρ, θυγᾰτέρος - daughter
ἀδελφός, ἀδελφή - brother, sister
λαός λαοῦ, ὁ - people, subjects

somewhat common in homer:
παρθένος (fem.) - virgin, unmarried girl
  https://archive.org/details/childrenshomerad00colu/page/138/mode/2up
  https://archive.org/details/childrenshomerad00colu/page/152/mode/2up
  https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:1878_Frederick_Leighton_-_Nausicaa.jpg
βασιλεύς βασιλέως, ὁ - https://archive.org/details/childrenshomerad00colu/page/32/mode/2up (is of Nestor)
ἔθνος ἔθνους, τό
γένος - race, stock, kin, https://logeion.uchicago.edu/%CE%B3%CE%AD%CE%BD%CE%BF%CF%82
δῆμος δήμου, ὁ - https://logeion.uchicago.edu/%CE%B4%E1%BF%86%CE%BC%CE%BF%CF%82 , district, country, land
ξένος ξένου, ὁ - guest-friend; foreigner, stranger
  https://archive.org/details/childrenshomerad00colu/page/190/mode/2up
δμώς, ὁ - slave taken in war; female house slave, e.g., Eurymedusa, Εὐρυμέδουσα, slave in Nausicaa's household, Odyssey 7.1
  may not always be clear which homeric characters were slaves;
               https://www.vox.com/identities/2017/11/20/16651634/odyssey-emily-wilson-translation-first-woman-english
  searches for "greek slave" turn up a famous american statue of a christian girl enslaved by turks
  many ancient images show slaves as smaller than masters, ew
  https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eumaeus#/media/File:Telemachus3511.gif -- Eumaios, the swinherd; positively portrayed; is he really a slave?
  https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Amphora_olive-gathering_BM_B226.jpg ... seems like the best

uncommon in homer:
πρέσβυς - old man, ambassador
  https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Phoenix_(son_of_Amyntor)
  https://archive.org/details/childrenshomerad00colu/page/62/mode/2up (is of Phoenix)
  https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Briseis_Phoinix_Louvre_G152.jpg (also of Phoenix)


